Construct a new `Pin<Ptr>` around a pointer to some data of a type that implements [`Unpin`](../marker/trait.Unpin.html "trait std::marker::Unpin").

Unlike `Pin::new_unchecked`, this method is safe because the pointer `Ptr` dereferences to an [`Unpin`](../marker/trait.Unpin.html "trait std::marker::Unpin") type, which cancels the pinning guarantees.

##### [¬ß](#examples)Examples

```
use std::pin::Pin;

let mut val: u8 = 5;

// Since `val` doesn't care about being moved, we can safely create a "facade" `Pin`
// which will allow `val` to participate in `Pin`-bound apis  without checking that
// pinning guarantees are actually upheld.
let mut pinned: Pin<&mut u8> = Pin::new(&mut val);
```

