Gets a shared reference to the pinned value this [`Pin`](struct.Pin.html "struct std::pin::Pin") points to.

This is a generic method to go from `&Pin<Pointer<T>>` to `Pin<&T>`. It is safe because, as part of the contract of `Pin::new_unchecked`, the pointee cannot move after `Pin<Pointer<T>>` got created. ‚ÄúMalicious‚Äù implementations of `Pointer::Deref` are likewise ruled out by the contract of `Pin::new_unchecked`.

